SUMMARY:Heart of the City Speakers Series : An Evening with Kate Robson
DESCRIPTION:An Evening with Kate Robson – Something to Hold Onto \nJoin Toronto psychotherapist Kate Robson for an inspiring evening as she shares insights from her book Something to Hold Onto. Packed with practical tools\, warm guidance\, and evidence-based strategies\, this talk is designed to support your mental and emotional well-being. Drawing on her experience with NICU families and high-stress environments\, Kate brings humour\, compassion\, and expert advice for anyone seeking connection and resilience. \nWhen: Wednesday\, March 25 | Time: 7 PM | Tickets: $10 \nThis event is open to everyone—everyone is welcome!
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/heart-of-the-city-speakers-series-an-evening-with-kate-robson/
LOCATION:St. Andrew’s Presbyterian Church\, 73 Simcoe St\, Toronto\, ON M5J 1W9\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M5J 1W9
CATEGORIES:Talks & Panels
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/heart-of-the-city-speakers-series-an-evening-with-kate-robson.png
END:VEVENT
